Module org.example.syllllogysme
Package traitement

Interface Validateur

All Known Implementing Classes:
Polysyllogisme, Syllogisme
public interface Validateur
Interface for validating logical rules in a syllogism. This interface defines methods to apply various logical rules and validate the syllogism.

  • Method Details

    • regleMoyenTerme

      void regleMoyenTerme()
      Applies the "Moyen Terme" rule. This rule checks the relationship of the middle term in the syllogism.

    • regleLatius

      void regleLatius()
      Applies the "Latius" rule. This rule checks if a universal term in the conclusion must also be universal in the premises.

    • rNN

      void rNN()
      Applies the "rNN" rule. This rule checks if both premises are negative, meaning no conclusion can be drawn.

    • rN

      void rN()
      Applies the "rN" rule. This rule checks if one premise is negative, the conclusion must also be negative.

    • rAA

      void rAA()
      Applies the "rAA" rule. This rule checks that if both premises are affirmative, the conclusion cannot be negative.

    • rPP

      void rPP()
      Applies the "rPP" rule. This rule checks that if both premises are particular, no valid conclusion can be drawn.

    • rP

      void rP()
      Applies the "rP" rule. This rule checks if a particular premise implies that the conclusion must also be particular.

    • rUU

      void rUU()
      Applies the "rUU" rule. This rule checks that if both premises are universal, the conclusion must also be universal.

    • valider

      Reponse valider()
      Validates the syllogism by applying the defined rules and returns the result.
      Returns:
      a response indicating whether the syllogism is valid or not.
